<paragraph id="8BEDF147D654DC1F22CEFCB3B3006440" blockId="19.[151,1437,152,1978]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<materialsCitation id="3B3AFB1AD654DC1F22CEFCB3B3056440" collectionCode="CB" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
Type specimens are greatly damaged, and we selected one better preserved female as 
<typeStatus id="54E94FE5D654DC1F26FFFCB3B76365D8" box="[1271,1383,152,178]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Holotype</typeStatus>
, the remaining specimens lacking abdomen, or one or both antennae, or one or more legs. The gonostyli and basal piece of the single male 
<typeStatus id="54E94FE5D654DC1F23BCFCC3B01F6468" box="[436,539,232,258]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Paratype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode id="ED436982D654DC1F2022FCC3B0576468" box="[554,595,232,258]" country="Australia" name="The CB Rhizobium Collection" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">CB</collectionCode>
) are lost, and its abdomen is damaged; so we figured only the aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="1369EDC2D654DC1F2297FD3BB2F26440" box="[159,246,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="20.[151,269,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[201,1390,364,1338]" captionTargetId="figure-251@20.[151,1436,314,1362]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Hycleus pintoi n. sp. 12. right elytron; 13. head, lateral view; 14. mesosternal sclerites; 15. apex of the aedeagus. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5103310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5103310/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
