<subSubSection id="C348A2CCD654DC1F22CEFD1CB0126700" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEDF147D654DC1F22CEFD1CB0126700" blockId="19.[151,1437,152,1978]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D654DC1F22CEFD1CB342643B" bold="true" box="[198,326,311,337]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
One 
<taxonomicName id="4C528AC4D654DC1F2386FD13B3E8643B" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[398,492,312,337]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D654DC1F2386FD13B3E8643B" box="[398,492,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belonging to the group of 
<emphasis id="B9262D55D654DC1F2148FD13B1E0643B" box="[832,996,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="4C528AC4D654DC1F2148FD13B1E4643B" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[832,992,312,337]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnipes">H. brunnipes</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
strictly related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C528AC4D654DC1F26C4FD13B33E6410" authority="Pardo Alcaide, 1968" authorityName="Pardo Alcaide" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaszabi">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D654DC1F26C4FD13B748643B" box="[1228,1356,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. kaszabi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC38CB6D654DC1F2750FD13B33E6410" author="Pardo Alcaide, A." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="623 - 629" refId="ref24040" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1968) Etude sur les Meloidae (Coleoptera). XX. Sur le genre Gorrizia Pardo et une nouvelle espece soudanaise du groupe du brunnipes (Klug). EOS, Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 43, 623 - 629." type="journal article" year="1968">Pardo Alcaide, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because of the depressed and flattened frons, clypeus on the same level of frons and legs almost completely red, except coxae and throcanters, but immediately distinct from this last species because of the following features: head more elongate, particularly labrum and clypeus, and consequently mandibles less visible outside of the labrum; frontal suture well visible; temples more parallel and less narrowed posteriorly; antennae black with only middle antennomeres vaguely reddish; last antennomere slightly more robust in the last third; head and pronotum puncturation denser; elytra brown and partially reddish with two fore black spots transverse and not oblique.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
